cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.DS

The paper discusses the use of neural networks in collaborative filtering, which is a subfield of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with recommendation systems, which falls under the category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The use of side information to improve the performance of the algorithm also suggests the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with large and sparse datasets, which could fall under the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the use of collaborative filtering in social networks, which could fall under the category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
